{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 MIDI CC to pitchbend\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This was designed to allow me to pitch bend my MIDI when the only useful pitch bend input was a CC converted from a gamepad joystick. The software I used to generate the CC was Fergo JoystickMIDI, with LoopBe1 to route it into Reaper.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Known bugs:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Bending all the way down to zero might accidentally reset the bend to 50% (no bend). This is because zero is also the value generated when the CC receives no input.\sa180\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 Description\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Listens to a CC on a specific route (Bus+Channel+CC), and transforms it into a "bistate button". Re-routing is possible.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Two modes are possible :\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab In "Push Button" mode, a MIDI Message is emitted when the input CC value passes across the threshold in both directions (if it's upwards, the "On" value is emitted on the output CC, and if it's downwards, the "Off" value is emitted).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab In "Toggle" mode, a MIDI Message is emitted when the input CC value passes across the threshold but only upwards. It the memorized state was "Off", the "On" value is emitted, and reversely.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 Reaper forum thread\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 https://forum.cockos.com/showthread.php?t=238532\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 \fmodern Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Midi CC Mapper X\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This JSFX is an extended version of the original plugin called "MIDI CC Mapper" with many more features. It allows to modify the behavior and the real-time feel of a MIDI controller, by acting as a pre-filter on the MIDI input. It can :\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Tweak CC (or Channel Pressure) / Pitch Bend / Keyboard Velocity / Poly After Touch response curves :\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab By using predefined curves, some of them being parametric\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab By pen-drawing/prototyping custom curves\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab By smoothing the current curve\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab By restricting the range of values of your curve\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab By extending the predefined curves with your own sets of functions (through lib files)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab The current curve can be exported and reused in your own sets\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Morph the response curves between a starting curve and an ending curve, with a morphing parameter\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab The morphing parameter can be automated\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab An auto-emit option is available to continuously fill the gaps with MIDI events when the morphing parameter changes\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Split/drop/channel re-route keyboard keys\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Transpose keyboard keys\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Re-route CCs / CP\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Re-route CC channels\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Conditionally channel re-route/drop CCs / CP / Pitch Bend / Velocity / Poly After Touch based on input/output values\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Pass through initial unmodified events (and act as a splitter)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Handle High-Res input and Output for the CCs (CC/CC+32) and Keyboard velocity (CC#88 format).\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The UI shows a virtual controller, on which CCs can be attributed to controls, allowing a user to visually map her/his real controller.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 High-Res MIDI input can be enabled via a global parameter, and High-Res MIDI output can be enabled on CCs individually.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Keyboard Filtering Module\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Located in the top left of the main window, it can be used to achieve keyboard splitting, up to five different ranges (green/red/blue/orange/purple). You can enable/disable the whole splitting configuration with the button located in the module title bar. If splitting is enabled, the keys can be colorized with the mouse by left/right clicking and moving the mouse on them while the mouse is down. The UI provides feedback for currently pressed keys on the MIDI Controller.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 An input channel may be defined for the keyboard, it may be "any" or a specific one : all other channels will be ignored by the plugin. Output channels may be defined for the each color range of the keyboard to possibly reroute them, with the option to drop each of them (to filter some keys out).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This module can be of great help for defining regions on the keyboard, especially when used on multiple tracks at the same time ; you can easily achieve left/right hand split, multi-instruments combinations and more. In addition to routing, each range has its own configuration for transposition, velocity response curve, and After-Touch response curve.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Keyboard Transposition Module\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Located in the top right of the main window. This module can be enabled or bypassed globally with the button located in the module title bar. If enabled, applies the sum of two parameters, one for transposing by octaves, one for transposing by semitones ; each keyboard color range has its own set of params and may be enabled/disabled individually.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 CC Routing/Curve tweaking\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Located in the bottom of the main window. This module UI is contextual to the selected control. When selected, a control can be enabled or disabled individually with the button located in the module title bar.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 There are 4 types of control, depending on the MIDI feature, which can be (from left to right) :\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Pitch Bend (1 pitch wheel)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab CC or Channel Pressure (1 mod wheel, 4 pedals, 10 faders, 10 knobs, 10 pads)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Velocity (5 Velocity controls, one for each keyboard color range)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab After-Touch (5 AfterTouch controls, one for each keyboard color range)\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For each control, the response curve :\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab can be defined from one of the templates on the right\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab can be pendrawn by hand with the mouse\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab can be smoothed with the smooth button\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab may be restricted to a user-defined space by configuring MIDI min/max values.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For CC (or CP) controls :\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A description can be given that will appear in the title bar\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A short description can be given that will appear close to the control for convenience\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab An input CC can be assigned (except for the velocity control which is tied to the keyboard velocity)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab This input CC can be CC learned\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab An output CC can be assigned\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab This output CC can be copied from the input CC\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Note that MIDI Channel Pressure is not technically a MIDI CC# and uses a different type of MIDI message. However, MIDI CC Mapper X unifies CC and CP by proposing a virtual "Channel Pressure" CC #128. If selected as input and routing is ok, messages of type Channel Pressure will be converted to CC messages and reversely if selected as output.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Additionally, for Pitch Bend and CC controls, channel routing may be achieved.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Morphing curves\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For each control, an additional response curve may be defined. The control will now used a morphed curve calculated from the start curve and this new end curve, using a morph parameter, which can be automated.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 An auto-emit option is available for standard controls (cc + pitch bend). This option will ensure that, if there was some activity on the control, and the morph parameter is moved (by automation, e.g.) some midi events will be forged and emitted to ensure the continuity of the MIDI flow.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Customizing the function library\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The function library is customizable. You can rearrange things, remove sets and functions, and add your own functions after having generated them or having exported them from REAPER. Please refer to the library manual, which is located in <REAPER_RESOURCE_PATH>/Data/talagan_MIDI CC Mapper X/README.md .\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Reaper forum thread\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 https://forum.cockos.com/showthread.php?t=172630\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Detailed PDF Documentation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 https://stash.reaper.fm/45839/MIDI%20CC%20Mapper%20X.pdf\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Notes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Older versions (v1 and v2) can be found on the forum thread.\par}
}

