{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Routter is a inter-track multichannel routing/mixing tool. A stereo track contains two channels, but REAPER supports up to 64 channels per track. Routter can route and blend the first 16 of them in many ways.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Copy, move, merge, replace, blend volume, mono/stereo, etc.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 INSTRUCTIONS:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Input Channels - Choose the channels you want to process. Click the title for channels 9-16. Set the volume for the processed channels with the slider next to the Input Channel selector. Stereo/Mono - Switches between selecting mono or stereo channels. Copy or Move - Chooses whether the original channels will be muted or not. To Channels - Chooses which channels the selected channels will be moved/blended to. Click the title for channels 9-16. Merge or Replace - Chooses whether the chosen channels will be blended or if they'll replace the To Channels. Original Volume - Sets the volume for the original To Channels (only in Blend mode).\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 Description\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The plugin works with four Midi Buses:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 "Command" accepts a definable Midi CC message to switch the routing to "low", "high" or "both", depending on the "Max Low" and "Min High" settings.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Midi message in the "In" Bus are routed to the "Low" and "High" out Buses appropriately.\line All messages other than "Note On" and "Hold Pedal=press" are sent to both out buses. "Note On" and "Hold Pedal=press" are sent according to the current routing definition state.\par}
}

