{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This is a Gain plugin with a VU meter and a feature to automatically match the output volume to a target level.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Gain - Allows you to manually change the gain.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Target Level - This is the level you want your volume level to be at. This will be a target for gain matching as well as a target for the 0 on the VU meter so that you can match the level manually. By default this is set to the standard -18db.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Gain Match - When you slide this over, it will set the gain so that the output level matches the target level and then it will immediately switch off.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 VU Speed - This is the speed/response of the VU meter\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 To achieve the most accurate results, set the gain to 0db and play/loop your track at its busiest/loudest point when you Gain Match. If the result isn't quite right, it may be because you matched if on significant dip/peak. You can set the Gain back to 0 and try again. Or if the result is just a little bit off, you can adjust the gain accordingly and watch the VU meter for reference to your Target level.\par}
}

